messages.text: Hi. I know you asked for time and I’m going to give it to you…
But I have to tell you something.
I already know.
You’re using me to get back at Scott. This was all a big game.
What? I would never. That’s not true.
So your girlfriend didn’t hit on Scott? And you didn’t get pissed at him?
You didn’t want to make him pay?
It’s a lot more complicated than that.
Is that woman still your girlfriend?
No. We broke up months ago.
Because of Scott?
That was part of it.
Skye cringes.
The reaction surprises her — she really didn’t want Scott’s words to be true.
How convenient then that his ex just happened to text you. I bet you loved that.
I did, Skye. But not because I wanted to get back at him…
Because I like you.
Sure. You must have liked having a weapon to use against Scott.
You know me. Does that sound like something I would do?
I don’t know. We haven’t spoken in years.
And even back then, it was just because I happened to be around your apartment all the time.
It wasn’t like that, and you know it.
I don’t know anything anymore.
Please, just hear me out.
I should have known he’d do something like this.
What are you talking about?
Scott.
I saw him this morning. I shouldn’t have said anything, but I did.
I told him you texted me by accident. And I told him I asked you out.
That’s why I was texting you now, even though I said I’d give you space. I wanted you to know I told him.
You told him?
Yes. I’m sorry. I don’t know if that was a mistake or not.
It just didn’t feel right keeping that from him.
I can’t stand Scott, but he IS my roommate.
Skye was confused before — but now, the feeling quadruples.
Had Scott known all along?
Was he lying…or is Caleb?
He said he had no idea we had been talking.
I promise you, Skye. I told him.
What time?
What do you mean?
What time did you tell him?
I guess it was just after 8, when he got back from the gym.
Skye checks her phone.
Scott’s first text was at 8:14 am
He HAD known about her texts with Caleb.
In fact, that must have been the reason he reached out to her.
That’s when he texted me. He acted like he didn’t know anything.
I’m sorry, Skye. I didn’t mean to make this harder for you.
Skye needs to hear from Scott.
She wants his side of the story, so she texts him and doesn’t pull any punches.
You knew.
Knew what?
Don’t play dumb. You lied. Caleb told you about our texts.
I don’t know what he’s telling you, but it’s bullshit.
Cut the crap, Scott.
He said he told you around 8. That’s *exactly* when you texted me.
If you tell me it’s a coincidence, I’m blocking your number.
Okay, relax.
She always hated when he’d tell her to relax.
Especially in a moment like now — when she has a right to be pissed.
It’s not like it seems.
Yeah? Because it seems like you lied to me.
Again.
I want you back—
And I thought if you knew he told me, you’d think that was the reason why I was contacting you.
It’s not, Skye. I just miss you.
You have a funny way of showing it.
What do you want me to say?
That I got jealous when I found out Caleb asked you out?
Well, I did.
Skye shakes her head.
I should have known.
But don’t you see? This is a good thing.
You lying to me is NOT a good thing.
I only did that so you wouldn’t be mad at me.
That clearly worked.
I see that now. But don’t you get it?
This whole mess made me realize how much I still want you.
Skye, I love you.
Don’t let something stupid stand in our way.
Scott…
I’m serious Skye. I love you.
Let me make this up to you—
Meet me tonight.
Skye had wanted to hear him say that he loved her since they broke up.
She looks at her phone.
What should she do?
She knows the answer—
Because there was never really a question.
Can you meet me at Wine and Kisses at 8?
